    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Bush Came to Tame His Inner Scamp'' (front page, July 29):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Bush Came to Tame His Inner Scamp'' (front page, July 29):</p>
        <p>Anyone who can sidle up to a 50-year-old matron and ask her about sex after 50 and who can ask the queen of England to divulge the black sheep in her family has a delightful and, yes, scampish sense of humor that says he is for real.</p>
        <p>For years, I have been delivering improbable and silly queries to the unsuspecting at unlikely moments and don't for a moment, at age 62, intend to give up my playful ways. Life can get awfully serious, and a little levity is needed every now and then.</p>
        <p>TED BACHE  Menlo Park, Calif., July 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
